<header class="[ intro intro--bgcolored-medium ] [ pad-top-900 pad-bottom-max ]">
  <div class="[ inner-wrapper ] [ sf-flow ]">
    <h1 class="[ intro__heading intro__heading--center ] [ pad-top-500 pad-bottom-500 text-800 md:text-900 leading-tight ] [ p-name ]">Superpower your GraphQL server</h1>
    <div class="[ nav ] [ md:box-flex ]">
      <div class="[ home__snippet md:width-twothirds pad-bottom-500 ]">
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">Code-first approach</strong><br/>
        The schema is generated from code. Work with your teammates concurrently on the schema without conflicts, and without depending on tooling.</p>
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">Native HTTP Caching</strong><br/>
        Cache the response from the query in several layers (server, CDN, etc) using standard HTTP caching. The max age is defined field by field.</p>
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">Schema multi-verse</strong><br/>
        Publish different schemas from a single source of truth, and give users access to them based on their being logged-in or not, user roles, having a PRO membership, and others.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="[ home__snippet md:width-third pad-bottom-500 pad-left-700 ]">
        <span class="[ home__logo ]" aria-hidden="true"><img src="/assets/batman.png"></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="[ nav ] [ md:box-flex bleed ]">
      <div class="[ home__snippet md:width-third pad-bottom-500 ]">
        <span class="[ home__logo ]" aria-hidden="true"><img src="/assets/superman.png"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="[ home__snippet md:width-twothirds pad-bottom-500 pad-left-700 ]">
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">Iterate quickly</strong><br/>
        React based on your user's feedback, immediately: create a specific resolver to fix a specific bug or create a specific feature for a specific client.</p>
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">Field/directive-based versioning</strong><br/>
        In addition to evolving the GraphQL schema, every field and directive can be independently versioned, and the specific version to use in the query is chosen through field/directive arguments.</p>
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">Automatic namespacing</strong><br/>
        Avoid conflicts from having 3rd party providers name their types the same way, and forget about adding <code>MyCompanyName</code> on your types.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="[ nav ] [ md:box-flex ]">
      <div class="[ home__snippet md:width-twothirds pad-bottom-500 ]">
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">REST from the same source of truth</strong><br/>
        Make your API available through REST endpoints for no extra cost, resolving them through GraphQL.</p>
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">Compatible with Serverless PHP</strong><br/>
        Components can be deployed on their own, with/out an underlying CMS. It's perfect for serverless!</p>
        <p class="[ pad-bottom-500 ] [ p-name ]">
        <strong class="[ leading-tight ]">A single query to rule them all</strong><br/>
        Resolve all your business logic in a single query: fetch data, combine it, fetch more data, and execute an action or two.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="[ home__snippet md:width-third pad-bottom-500 pad-left-700 ]">
        <span class="[ home__logo ]" aria-hidden="true"><img src="/assets/ironman.png"></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="[ home__snippet home__snippet--center pad-bottom-300 ]">
      <a class="[ button text-500 ]" href="/learn">Learn more</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>
